        <h1>Edge proportion</h1>

        <p>This tool will measure the edge proportion, i.e. the proportion of 
            grid cells in a polygon that are located along the polygon's boundary, 
            for an input raster image. Edge proportion is an indicator of polygon 
            shape complexity and elongation. The user must specify the name of the 
            output raster file, which will be raster layer containing the input 
            features assigned the edge proportion. The user may also optionally 
            choose to output text data for easy input to a spreadsheet or 
            database.</p>

